news.title: Bombay HC registers new petition over illegal constructions in Goa
news.para: Advocate general Devidas Pangam told reporters that the high court is concerned about all illegal constructions by the side of roads, in coastal regulation zones (CRZ), and within the jurisdictions of panchayats and municipalities.

news.title: About 110 government buildings in Ghaziabad yet to pay nearly Rs 300 crore municipal taxes
news.para: GMC's chief tax assessment officer Sanjeev Singh said a central govt rule mandates municipalities across the country to levy service charges for services, like roads, water, drainage networks and streetlights, on all central and state govt buildings and installations.

news.title: Will support genuine builders: Telangana CM
news.para: Sources told TOI that realtors and developers recently expressed significant concerns to ministers about the negative impact on the real estate sector stemming from the feared demolitions related to the HYDRA initiative.

news.title: About 81 homebuyers of Eldeco Aamantran in Noida get documents
news.para: While the developer did not opt for the UP govt's rehabilitation scheme for stalled projects due to relatively low dues, officials said the camp was held in line with the state's directive to facilitate doorstep property registrations.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM will open mini-IT park in Tuticorin soon: Industries minister
news.para: The park was established at a cost of 30 crore. Spread across 4.16 acres, the multi-storey mini-IT park is set to offer 50,937sqft of leasable state-of-the-art workspace, equipped with amenities like air conditioning and an integrated building management system (IBMS).

news.title: Registrations of properties in Pune dip 33% to 11,056 units in September
news.para: "In September 2024, Pune recorded 11,056 property sale registrations, marking a 33% decline compared to the same period last year," Knight Frank India said in a statement on Saturday.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat's profit declines 60.2% to Rs 49 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Its revenue from operations was also down 2.09 per cent to Rs 3,087 crore during the quarter under review. It was at Rs 3,153 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal year.

news.title: Many construction & demolition projects in Haryana yet to register on portal
news.para: The portal, inaugurated by the state govt in Jan 2022 for real-time monitoring of pollution levels at C&D sites, is yet to witness registration from a substantial number of such sites, "which is a matter of grave concern".

news.title: Kerala: Demolition of buildings set to begin for Vattiyoorkavu junction project
news.para: he demolition will take a month to complete. The tender to select the contractor for the demolition works will be finalized within a week, as the last date for the tender submission was on Friday.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government allows free transportation of sand in tractors
news.para: After receiving complaints from the public about the high-handed approach of officials and legislators at some places, the chief minister made it clear that there should not be any hurdles in implementation of free sand policy.

news.title: DDA finalises maintenance plan for civic services at Jasola HIG flats
news.para: While DDA is still corresponding with Municipal Corporation of Delhi to take over the sanitation services in these pockets, it has decided to choose agencies to perform these tasks for a year for the convenience of the residents.

news.title: CBI raids multiple locations in Rajasthan over illegal sand mining
news.para: The raids were carried out at the residential and official premises of some people suspected of involvement in the case, covering areas in Jaipur, Tonk, Ajmer and Bhilwara. During the searches, the CBI recovered incriminating documents related to illegal sand mining operations.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body's new norms make it challenging to operate PGs: Owners
news.para: Their three major concerns are requirement to store CCTV footage for 90 days instead of 30, as mandated previously by police department; providing 70 square feet of space per inmate; deploying mandatory security personnel, which they say will cost them more and many PG managements won't be able to afford the same.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires three acres land in Ahmedabad
news.para: The project comprises of residential apartments of various configurations with an estimated booking value of Rs 1,300 crore.

news.title: Legal status of land parcels to soon be available online in Maharashtra
news.para: The land records department has started to include data of civil court cases related to plots in the city and rural areas on its website. The process of integration has been going for over a year. Some data has already been linked.

news.title: Bombay HC orders flat allotment to former mill worker
news.para: The rehabilitation project was in Lower Parel, at the Prakash Cotton Mill compound, and the high court was critical of the state for not having considered the hardship suffered by the former senior citizen mill worker and many others like him.

news.title: SC recalls 2022 verdict declaring benami law provisions unconstitutional
news.para: Allowing the Centre's review of the August 23, 2022 verdict, a bench Chief Justice of India (CJI) D Y Chandrachud, Justices P S Narasimha and Manoj Misra recalled the judgement delivered by a three-judge bench headed by former CJI N V Ramana.

news.title: ED issues eviction notice against Supreme Construction's director in PMLA case
news.para: ​​It was alleged that Supreme Construction & Developer Pvt Ltd (SCDPL), a company controlled by Tekchandani and others, collected Rs 400 crore from several homebuyers for a housing project in Taloja, Navi Mumbai.
